data.title: Selected Goods for the Independent Mind
data.meta_description: Your online store for curated fashion lifestyle goods and homeware. Fast worldwide shipping from London UK.
data.text:
UNDERDAYS

Pairing luxury fabrics with world-class design, Underdays is the first underwear brand to turn underwear into self-care because they believe you deserve underwear products that are just as high-performing and good-looking as whats on your bathroom shelf. No more compromises between comfort and style. Now as one of their first stockist, Goodhood welcome another great new, independent brand to our collection.

SHOP UNDERDYAS

NACHE

Nache clothing focuses on creating unisex apparel that blends avant-garde and casual styles, characterised by unsecured and deformable silhouettes that adapt to the moment. Their designs aim for a continuous and dynamic aesthetic in fashion. Exclusively stocked by Goodhood in the UK.

SHOP NACHE

HOMMEGIRLS

Introducing Hommegirls, originally the brand was highlighted as the new passion project of designer Thakoon Panichgul, now multimedia fashion platform. The designs are inspired by and dedicated to women that shop in the mens department. They produce a mix of street style, vintage celebrity inspo and iconic fashion editorials. Thakoon takes inspiration from stylish women such as Brana Wolf and Grace Coddington and now we are thrilled to share it at Goodhood.

SHOP HOMMEGIRLS

BRAIN DEAD

Brain Dead is a creative collective of artists and contributors from around the world. With influences rooted in post-punk culture, underground comics and skateboarding, Brain Deads disruptive graphic identity is conceived. Not one person, nor is it one idea, Brain Dead sits in the space between people, being a favourite for graphic adorned clothing and playful t-shirts.

SHOP BRAIN DEAD

RAYON VERT

Rayon Vert stands out with their innovative approach to production, involving consumers in the process to reforge a meaningful connection with their apparel and gear. Their collection adds a perfect elevation to clothing that is designed with functionality in mind.

SHOP RAYON VERT

HAY

Inspired by the innovation and greatness of Danish furniture and interior design of the 1950's and 60's, HAY work with an international roster of the best names in interiors and furniture design, while harbouring new and up and coming talent. HAY operates in the field between architecture and fashion bridging the statics from architecture and the dynamics from fashion. HAY are ambitious in the field of innovation and the use of cutting edge technology with an aesthetic that is Scandinavian through and through; simple, straight forward, functional and joyful.

SHOP HAY

TEENAGE ENGINEERING

Teenage Engineering creates high quality, well designed, electronic products for all people who love sound and music. Founded in 2005 in Sweden by Jesper Kouthoofd, David Eriksson, Jens Rudberg and David Mllerstedt, they have created world-leading and award winning synthesisers and audio equipment that are ground-breaking in function and design.

SHOP TEENAGE ENGINEERING

HIGHTIDE PENCO

Founded in 1994 in Fukuoka, Japan, this humble stationery brand has quickly grown in popularity and is now recognised throughout the world. As with many Japanese brands, the attention to detail and product design innovations are of paramount importance. Included in the Hightide family is Penco, riffing off the iconic ballpoint pen and redesigning it with a Japanese eye.

SHOP HIGHTIDE PENCO

WE HAVE TO CREATE CULTURE

The words and learnings from ethnobotanist Terence McKenna are important to us. He once said Culture is not your friend and believed we should create our own experiences and communities instead of consuming the ones projected by the mass media. This quote inspired by him is printed on the walls of our store and are a great reminder that we need to create our own culture. Important now more than ever.

SHOP GOODS BY GOODHOOD

GOODHOOD X ED DAVIS

Are you a Dissident? Well you should be... Check out some more mind altering graphics on a plethora of homeware. As an further part of our special collaboration with Ed Davis we have added more of his graphics to some of our favourite homeware pieces with a selection of mugs, ashtrays, stickers and slipmats.

SHOP GOODHOOD X ED DAVIS

THE PERFECT WHITE T-SHIRT

So simple yet by virtue of its simplicity so hard to get right. What makes the perfect white tee? Fabric, fit and detailing of course but its in the minutiae of the details where we find the joy. In short, this essential wardrobe staple converges the best of t-shirt detailing into, in our humble opinion, the best white tees on the market.

SHOP GOODS BY GOODHOOD

GOOD VIBES 115 - LAUER

Our latest Good Vibes comes from none other than prolific German Producer & DJ Lauer. Conceived as more of a mixtape leading us into springtime, and the longer days ahead lying in the sun, Lauer takes us all on a transcendent journey through some of his current favourite tracks...

LISTEN

GOOD VIBES 113 - ANU

DJ, illustrator and NTS resident Anu is next up on our Good Vibes roster. Blending an eclectic mix of sounds, her self-discovery through music brings a varied range of genres to her mixes. Tune in now...

LISTEN

GOOD VIBES 112 - MICHAEL KOPELMAN

Gimme 5 just launched their 'Icon' collection. To celebrate the moment, we've enlisted Michael Kopelman, founder of Gimme 5 and UK streetwear originator, to put together a Good Vibes mix for your listening pleasure.

LISTEN

AUDIOPHILES: A LIFESTYLE

Audiophiles: a Lifestyle Audiophile by dictionary defintion: a person who is very interested in and enthusiastic about equipment for playing recorded sound, and it's quality. Sound familiar? Keep reading, this ones for you. We break down world-class music paraphernalia, why we love it, and why you should love it too.

EXPLORE NOW

THE CULTURAL IMPACT LARRY OF CLARKS' KIDS WITHIN STREETWEAR

Kids contains themes of sex, drugs, theft and violence, the film is often labelled as controversial and exploitative, which aren't exactly unreasonable comments. But there's no denying that Kids has had a monumental cultural impact on streetwear. We break down what sets it apart from the rest.

EXPLORE NOW

LONDON'S FORGOTTEN CLUBS

"The best days have been and gone", or that's what we always seem to hear, at least. That the London club scene isn't what it once was. Is that actually true? We break down "the good old days" of London club culture...

EXPLORE NOW

FROM GORPCORE TO GOMMCORE: GOOD OL' MUSHROOMS AND MAGIC

Gorpcore; whether you love it or hate it, it doesn't look like the peoples love for time spent outdoors is dropping off any time soon, and we can see why. It's a yes from us, only, we like to think of Gorp as less Good Old Raisins and Peanuts, and more Good Old Mushrooms and Magic.

EXPLORE NOW
